2007-08-16
  * lib/cmt/oop_mod.pm:
	can't shift @_ because $_[i] is in used in the semantic actions.

  * source.bat:
	- accepts a filename as source
	- no setlocal, so environment changes are took affected. But when source.bat is used in pipe-mode, this doesn't work. (maybe the source.bat is executed in a separated process, so it can't modify the current process(shell)'s environment. )

  * relay.pl:
	add --rawdump=charrange to suppress some unwanted chars(like \a beep) for reading purpose.

  * lib/cmt/oop_mod.pm:
	@_ includes "yylval" in semantic actions, so the first component is shifted out.

  * lib/cmt/: oop_y.pm, oop_y.y:
	- using more strict grammer, don't use empty=() any more.
	- also repeat-delimiter can't be empty.
	- carefully adjusted the precedence, so all conflicts are resolved as supposed.

  * lib/cmt/perlsys.pm:
	which_sub now supports to specify the sub by name.

  * lib/cmt/oop.pm:
	- catch 'die' from Yapp::Driver.
	- output diagnostic info only if any warnings.

